President Muhammed Buhari is expected to visit Lagos on Tuesday to unveil the plaque inaugurating Dangote Fertilizer Plant and inspect Lekki Sea Port, SaharaReporters gathered. According to a programme document obtained by this newspaper, Buhari will do a factory tour of the Dangote TPA Fertilizer plant, and inspect the 650,000 BPO oil refinery and 900,000 TPA Polypropylene Plant.  He will subsequently move to the Lekki Deep Sea Port for proper inspection and return to the Helipad at the Dangote Fertiliser Plant for departure from Lagos. Meanwhile, the tour and inspection are scheduled from 10: 10 am on Tuesday to 12:30 pm. The visit comes after the Presidentâ€™s return to the country last Friday from a medical trip to London on March 6.